<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210657>
    bibo:endPage "22" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "14" ;
    bibo:volume "3566" ;
    dc:creator "Hayat, Mohammad" ;
    dc:date "2012" ;
    dc:title "On some Encyrtidae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea) associated with gall-inducing psylloids, Phacopteron and Trioza species (Hemiptera: Phacopteronidae, Triozidae) in southern India" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210658>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210659> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210658>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8 – 14. Syrphophagus wayanadensis Hayat, sp. nov. Female: 8, antenna; 9, mandibles; 10, basal part of fore wing; 11, ovipositor; 12, hypopygium. Male: 13, distal part of genitalia; 14, antenna." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/210658/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210659>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21 – 25. Psylloid galls: 21, Syzygium caryophyllatum leaf with galls; 22, S. caryophyllatum, galls cut open to show developing psylloids; 23, S. cumini leaf galls; 24, Trioza jambolanae Crawford, adult; 25, Garuga pinnata, leaf galls. (Photographs by M. Nasser)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/210659/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

